**Coterminal angles** share the same 
terminal side when placed in standard position. Two angles are coterminal 
if they differ by a multiple of $360°$ (or $2\pi$ radians):
\[
 \theta \text{ and } \theta + 360°n \quad \text{(degrees)}
\]
\[
 \theta \text{ and } \theta + 2\pi n \quad \text{(radians)}
\]
where $n$ is any integer.
